# Dysphor App Models

This file outlines the data models that will be used in the Dysphor app.

## Pomodoro Models

### PomodoroSettings
```dart
class PomodoroSettings {
  final int workDuration;      // In minutes
  final int breakDuration;     // In minutes
  final int longBreakDuration; // In minutes
  final int sessionsBeforeLongBreak;
}
```

### PomodoroSession
```dart
class PomodoroSession {
  final String id;
  final String title;
  final String duration;
  final DateTime completedAt;
}
```

## Milestone Model

### Milestone
```dart
class Milestone {
  final String id;
  final String title;
  final String description;
  final DateTime targetDate;
}
```

## Data Persistence

All models will be persisted using `shared_preferences` rather than a full database solution. 

For JSON serialization, models should include manual toJson/fromJson methods instead of using the Freezed package or part syntax.
